== Personal life ==
[[File:David_et_Cathy_Guetta_NRJ_Music_Awards_2012.jpg|thumb|Guetta and his then-wife Cathy in January 2012 at the [[NRJ Music Awards]]]]
Guetta married nightclub manager [[Cathy Guetta|Cathy Lobé]] in 1992. They have two children: son Tim Elvis Eric (born 9 February 2004) and daughter Angie (born 23 September 2007).<ref>{{cite news|title=Cathy et David Guetta à nouveau parents|url= http://fr.news.yahoo.com/ap/20070924/ten-celebrites-guetta-bebe-9b325ba_1.html|agency=Associated Press |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20070925085900/http://fr.news.yahoo.com/ap/20070924/ten-celebrites-guetta-bebe-9b325ba_1.html|date=24 September 2007|archive-date=25 September 2007|language=fr}}</ref> After twenty-two years of marriage, the Guettas divorced in a Paris court in March 2014.<ref name="4music">{{cite episode|title=This Week's Fresh Music|network=[[4Music]]|series=This Week's Fresh Music Top 20|airdate=10 August 2014}}</ref> Neither party was present at the hearing and the reason for their divorce is unknown.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/03/24/david-guetta-wife_n_5022234.html|title=David Guetta And Wife Divorce After Two Decades of Marriage|date=24 March 2014|access-date=15 September 2018|work=[[Huff Post]]}}</ref>

In 2015, ''[[Forbes]]'' estimated that Guetta's annual income was $37 million.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.forbes.com/profile/david-guetta/ |title=David Guetta |website=[[Forbes]] |year=2015 |access-date=28 April 2016}}</ref>

